The Johannesburg Metro Police Department is conducting a major taxi blitz on Wednesday. JOHANNESBURG - The Johannesburg Metro Police Department is conducting a major taxi blitz on Wednesday. Authorities are targeting minibus-taxis that drive on the wrong side of Beyers Naude Drive. READ: Mbalula scraps old taxis JMPD spokesperson Wayne Minnaar says there have already been some taxi drivers breaking the law on Beyers Naude Drive at the N1 bridge in Fairlands. "One driver will also have to be charged for bribery because he tried to bribe on the officers with R100. This is a hotspot." Watch JMPD spokesperson Wayne Minnaar's full interview above.